This code replicates the results of the paper "Segmentation CNNs are denoising models".


The toy dataset for the experiments in the paperis based on the BraTS 2021 challenge, which
can be download at http://braintumorsegmentation.org/ and cited with the references below.

[1] U.Baid, et al., "The RSNA-ASNR-MICCAI BraTS 2021 Benchmark on Brain Tumor Segmentation
  and Radiogenomic Classification", arXiv:2107.02314, 2021(opens in a new window).
[2] B. H. Menze, A. Jakab, S. Bauer, J. Kalpathy-Cramer, K. Farahani, J. Kirby, et al.
  "The Multimodal Brain Tumor Image Segmentation Benchmark (BRATS)", IEEE Transactions on
  Medical Imaging 34(10), 1993-2024 (2015) DOI: 10.1109/TMI.2014.2377694 (opens in a new window)
[3] S. Bakas, H. Akbari, A. Sotiras, M. Bilello, M. Rozycki, J.S. Kirby, et al., "Advancing
  The Cancer Genome Atlas glioma MRI collections with expert segmentation labels and radiomic
  features", Nature Scientific Data, 4:170117 (2017) DOI: 10.1038/sdata.2017.117


The referred dataset has been pre-processed according to the specifications in the paper. 
Due to the large filesize, the pre-processed dataset could not be added to this reporsitory.
As a workaround, the dataset can be downloaded at
* https://drive.google.com/file/d/1QGluZ3MszzpJyvXxIIAACbKOkPjPNI8y/view?usp=drive_link.
